    "description": {
      "es": "",
      "en": "Decorator to indicate that a class, function or overload is deprecated. When this decorator is applied to an object, deprecation warnings may be emitted at runtime when the object is used. static type checkers will also generate a diagnostic on usage of the deprecated object. Usage: from warnings import deprecated from typing import overload @deprecated(\"Use B instead\") class A: pass @deprecated(\"Use g instead\") def f(): pass @overload @deprecated(\"int support is deprecated\") def g(x: int) ->..."
